function Section({ title, count, collapsed, onToggle, collapsible = true, action, children }) {
  return (
    <div className={styles.section}>
      <button ... className={styles.sectionHeader} ...>
        <span className={styles.chevron}>...</span>
        <span className={styles.sectionTitle}>{title}</span>
        {count !== undefined && <span className={styles.count}>{count}</span>}
      </button>
      {action && (
        <button className={styles.addBtn} onClick={action.onClick} title={action.title}>
          {/* Plus SVG icon */}
          <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" className={styles.addBtnIcon} aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M8 3v10M3 8h10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor"
                  strokeWidth="1.5" strokeLinecap="round" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      )}
      {!collapsed && children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

Important layout detail: The section header becomes a flex container with the add button positioned via `margin-left: auto` before the count badge, or the header row is wrapped in a flex container that holds both the button and the action. The cleaner approach: make the section header area a flex row with the toggle button on the left and the add action on the right.

